snippet.textDisplay:
I watched Love is Blind to get some perspective- if a reality show could prove that love could be blind. I was taken by you two automatically; I didn't agree with you guys going to bed so quick after...but to each his own. In Canada interracial marriages is no biggy here, I just find that Americans are so shocked by people genuinely loving one another regardless of race.
Why does who one loves have to be soooooo taboo- when it comes to racial differences.. One thing I have to say- don't make your channel about your racial differences- display the respect, understanding and the love that brought you both to where you are. Yes, you will face race issues,-just don't waste your energy on it; it is too big an issue that will destroy you if are too busy trying to fix everyone's view about it.
I wish you both a marriage that is forever real and true, and that you both always support and love one another for all of your days. A true fan.
